<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colosio Continues Campaign, Meets With Railroad Union </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001164394 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
1300 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Upon Awakening" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Luis Donaldo Colosio, the PRI [Institutional 
Revolutionary Party] presidential candidate, is continuing his 
political campaign. On 6 January he met with leaders from the 
Union of Railroad Workers of the Republic of Mexico [STFRM] and 
told them that economic competitiveness, improved trade 
procedures, and increasingly efficient services would be 
inconceivable without the railroad industry. He emphasized that 
the railroad sector must play a very important role in 
turn-of-the-century Mexico. Colosio pledged to promote a new 
phase of regional development in Mexico in which the railroad 
will be fundamental. 
  The presidential candidate asserted that Mexico will become 
stronger as its regions become more closely integrated, thereby 
increasing and improving trade. Colosio described the railroad 
workers as heirs of the tradition, effort, and tenacity to 
promote Mexico's growth. 
  The STFRM's national leader Antonio Castellanos Tovar spoke 
on the union's behalf. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

