<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   PGR Denies Giving Daily List of Rebel Leaders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001162594 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 0400 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 0400 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "TV-13 Sunday" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The daily EXCELSIOR published today a report on the 
alleged leaders of the armed groups in Chiapas. The report 
contains a list attributed to the Attorney General's Office 
[PGR] that includes priests, legislators, teachers, and PRD 
[Party of the Democratic Revolution] figures are among the rebel 
leaders. 
  Attorney General Jorge Carpizo today sent a letter to 
EXCELSIOR editor Regino Diaz Redondo stating that the PGR has 
not provided that information. It is obvious, Carpizo indicated 
in his letter, that the document does exist, but it has not come 
from the PGR. The official added that as far as he an the PGR 
are concerned, having a series of rumors and false statements 
attributed to them constitutes the most serious blow that could 
be dealt. Carpizo said the rumors are intended to destroy what 
has been built through much toil and that they harm the 
foundation for dispensing justice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

