<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pursuit of Rebels Continues in Altos de Chiapas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001145294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001145294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Javier de la Torre; from the "Good Morning From </F>
Mexico" newscast] 
  [Excerpt] The Army is continuing to pursue the rebels in 
Altos de Chiapas. The clashes have not stopped, especially near 
San Cristobal de las Casas. The first signs of an eventual 
dialogue with the armed groups have emerged. 
  The clashes continued between the Army and the rebels in Los 
Altos de Chiapas for the eighth consecutive day. The Army has 
repelled a rebel attack against the Rancho Nuevo Military 
Barracks near San Cristobal de las Casas. The roads to the 
areas of conflict remain closed. 
  During the pursuit operations, authorities found a Pemex 
[Mexican Petroleum] vehicle from which the rebels stole 1.5 tons 
of dynamite 31 December. The truck was found in Guadalupe 
Tepeyac, a town thought to be the rebels' stronghold, where it 
has been confirmed they are still holding captive the former 
Chiapas State governor, Absalon Castellanos, and approximately 
100 social security employees of the town. Thousands of Indians 
and peasants are fleeing from the areas of conflict to seek 
refuge in San Cristobal de las Casas, a city being reinforced by 
the Army. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

