<H3> <TI>   Attorney General's Office Remands 8 Rebels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001155994 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Attorney General's Office has taken legal action 
against eight rebels arrested in Chiapas. The eight rebels have 
said they were led by Commander Marcos, a Guatemalan, and (Jesus 
Meza Yaladaqui), also a Guatemalan. The arrested were remanded 
under the charges of homicide, infliction of injuries, criminal 
association, and the use of regulation weapons exclusive to the 
Army. 
  The First District judge in Tuxtla Gutierrez has remanded 
another group of 18 rebels. 

</TEXT>

