<H3> <TI>   Candidates Review Chiapas Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001151694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] PAN [National Action Party] presidential candidate 
Diego Fernandez de Cevallos has begun his political campaign in 
the city of Queretaro. Speaking to some 2,000 supporters, 
Fernandez de Cevallos referred to events in Chiapas by saying 
that bullets have to be used before people can understand that 
true social peace can only be achieved through justice. 
  Meanwhile, PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] 
presidential candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio today will begin his 
political campaign in Huejutla, Hidalgo State. Colosio also 
will visit Ciudad Valle, San Luis Potosi, Queretaro, Pachuca, 
Hidalgo, and Ecatepec in Mexico State before returning to Mexico 
City on 14 January. 
  PRD [Party of the Democratic Revolution] presidential 
candidate Cuauhtemoc Cardenas decided to postpone this week's 
scheduled trip to Sinaloa and Jalisco to remain in Mexico City 
and monitor developments in Chiapas. Cardenas will visit Colima 
State on 15 and 16 January. 

</TEXT>

