<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cosep President Urges UNO To Rejoin National Assembly </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1101043094 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1101043094 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Ramiro Gurdian Ortiz, president of the Higher 
Council of Private Enterprise [Cosep], has urged the National 
Opposition Union [UNO] deputies to rejoin the National Assembly 
as of Monday, when the 10th legislative session of the 
Nicaraguan parliament begins. 
  During a meeting held this past weekend, the business leader 
made the request to the 22 deputies who continue with their UNO 
strategy. Cosep President Gurdian Ortiz pointed out, however, 
that the businessmen are not taking sides in the strategy by the 
UNO deputies who are struggling to call for a constituent 
assembly in Nicaragua. 

</TEXT>

