<H3> <TI>   Salinas Meets Salvadoran, Honduran Presidents </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801031894 Mexico City Radio Mil Network in Spanish 2330 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0801031894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio Mil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ricardo Trejos from "The City" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari met a few 
minutes ago with Salvadoran President Alfredo Cristiani and 
Honduran President Rafael Leonardo Callejas. This meeting had 
been agreed upon in early December 1993. 
  The meeting, which lasted a couple of hours, was held at the 
official residence of Los Pinos in an atmosphere of cordiality 
and frankness. They reviewed the regional situation, bilateral 
relations, the outlook for the free trade agreement, and various 
topics of interest to the three countries, as is explained in a 
communique issued a few minutes ago by the Presidency General 
Media Directorate. The governments expressed their desire to 
cooperate and to provide mutual support to achieve greater 
development in the region. 
  The Salvadoran and Honduran presidents will return to their 
countries today. The communique does not specify whether the 
presidents discussed the topic of Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

