<H3> <TI>   New Colorado Party Executive Board Members Confirmed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1101174194 Asuncion HOY in Spanish 11 Jan 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PY1101174194 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion HOY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] During a special session, the Colorado Party 
Executive Board on 10 January confirmed Eugenio Sanabria Cantero 
as Colorado Party president, abiding by party statutes. The ANR 
[National Republican Association -- Colorado Party] therefore 
reshuffled its Executive Board after [former party President] 
Blas N. Riquelme's resignation. 
  In descending order, the post of first vice president went 
to 
Juan Manuel Cano Melgarejo, the post of second vice president 
went to Enrique Gonzalez Quintana, and the post of third vice 
president went to Juan Carlos Galaverna, who was supported by 
the majority of the 64 members present. 
  In addition, the post of political secretary went to 
Cristina 
Munoz, who is the first woman to occupy this post. 
  The session was held in a calm atmosphere and most 
secretaries of state participated. [passage omitted] 

