<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sailors Report Attempted Manipulation by ITF </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1101214594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1101214594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The motor vessel (Brothers) has arrived in port in 
Cuba after a 15-month voyage, during which time its crew bravely 
confronted a seige by officials of the International Transport 
Workers Federation, ITF, who tried to manipulate our sailors, 
making them out to be demanding salaries and other such things. 
The incident occurred in the Norwegian port of (Aldratagen), 
where the (Brothers) arrived carrying a shipment of aluminum 
powder for a factory located there. For several days, they were 
beseiged by the gentlemen from the ITF, who tried to make the 
Cubans out to be strikers demanding salaries. The staunch unity 
of the vessel's 28 crew members and their powerful response was 
not long in coming, and by means of placards and statements to 
the press and to television -- means that were also used by the 
ITF people to coerce them -- the Cubans denied the fib. 
  The (Brothers) returned victorious, and is now in the port 
of 
Cienfuegos unloading 22,000 tons of rice from Indonesia. There 
we spoke with officers and crew members as well as with the 
vessel's captain, Rogelio Rivero, who gave us this information 
for the National Radio Newscast. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

