<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   PRC Assists in Electric Motor Production </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1101195094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1255 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1101195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] With support from 24 advisors from the PRC, the 
first five low-voltage electric motors have been produced. These 
motors constitute a successful test prior to the adjustment 
phase of the factory that is being built in Cacocum, Holguin 
Province, with PRC cooperation. 
  The new electric motor factory is scheduled to begin 
operations during the first quarter of 1994. It is 72-percent 
complete, and its 120 basic machine tools are already installed. 
The first of these factories of moderate technological 
complexity in the country has the means necessary to annually 
produce 30,000 top-quality triphasic and monophasic motors of 23 
types, motors that will fulfill vital requirements in such 
economic sectors as the sugar and the nickel industries. The 
factory also opens horizons for exports and for penetration into 
the home electrical appliance field in Cuba. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

