<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stock Market Drops Due to Chiapas Conflict </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1101142694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1101142694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Mexican Stock Market registered its largest drop 
in the last four years. The main indicator pertaining to stock 
exchange transactions dropped 165.92 points, 6.3 percent, to 
close the day at 2459.52. Stock market analysts have said the 
atmosphere of uncertainty in our country as a result of the 
conflict in Chiapas has caused the drop in the stock market. 
They have warned about the possibility of a flight of capital 
and investments if the conflict prolongs or extends to other 
regions of the country. 

</TEXT>

