<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Says EZLN Acting Against NAFTA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001204094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1943 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1001204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 10 Jan (EFE) -- Eloy Cantu, official 
Mexican Government spokesman on the Chiapas conflict, said the 
armed uprising of the Zapatist National Liberation Army (EZLN) 
is intended to cloud and block the development of the North 
American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA). 
  In statements published today by the Mexican newspapers 
REFORMA and EL NORTE, Cantu indicated that the rebels seek to 
internationally discredit President Carlos Salinas de Gortari's. 
He said the rebels want to prevent free trade, the creation of 
jobs, the increase of foreign investments, economic growth, and 
wage increases in Mexico, objectives that NAFTA seeks. 
  "It is obvious that it is not an Indian insurgent movement, 
because if it were, they would be using machetes. This armed 
group would not have been repudiated as it has," he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

