<H3> <TI>   Released Hostages Arrive in Las Margaritas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1101155894 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
1300 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1101155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ricardo Pena from Tuxtla Gutierrez; from the </F>
"Upon Awakening" newscast] 
  [Text] Forty of the 100 individuals who were held against 
their will by rebel groups in Guadalupe Tepeyac, Las Margaritas 
Municipality, arrived early this morning. These individuals 
arrived yesterday [as heard] from that area, after they were 
released; in addition, 60 others who were held hostage at the 
Social Security Hospital in that area were also released. They 
all said they were held against their will. Relatives of the 
doctors and nurses who could not leave the town since 30 
December were also accompanying them. 
  Apparently, that area is still under rebel control. It is 
expected that the situation here will be normalized very soon, 
within a few hours or days, as the rebels will withdraw to the 
highlands in Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

