<H3> <TI>   Rebels Said To Retake Municipality </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1101192494 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1836 GMT 11 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1101192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, 11 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- 
Witnesses are reporting that an armed group of the self-styled 
Zapatist National Liberation Army (EZLN) took over for the 
second time Chanal Municipality, southeastern Chiapas State, 
early this morning. 
  A "large" number of EZLN members occupied Chanal, which had 
been retaken by the Mexican Army five days ago. The reports do 
not mention whether there is fighting. Chanal is located 
approximately 50 km east of San Cristobal de las Casas, which is 
located 1,200 km southeast of Mexico City and which was one of 
the municipalities seized by the armed group on 1 January, when 
the conflict began. 
  In a new operation, the Mexican Army is about 75 km from the 
town of Guadalupe Tepeyac, which, according to witnesses, has 
been cut off by armed men who dug five-meter deep trenches 
around it. 
  According to the reports, Guadalupe Tepeyac has been under 
the control of the armed group since 1 January, when the 
conflict began with the violent seizure of towns and an attack 
against a garrison, forcing the Army to intervene. 
  Witnesses say the armed group is preventing people from 
entering or leaving the center of Guadalupe Tepeyac, southeast 
Chiapas, near the Guatemalan border. Approximately 80 workers 
of the public clinic in Guadalupe Tepeyac were released 
yesterday by the armed group and are in Tuxtla Gutierrez, 
capital of Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

