<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy Grants 10-Day Leave To Ease Economic Woes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1101001394 Montevideo BUSQUEDA in Spanish 5 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PY1101001394 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo BUSQUEDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Navy gave a leave of absence for almost 10 days 
to the majority of its personnel in order to make savings and to 
alleviate a difficult economic situation "caused by the current 
circumstances," Navy sources have told BUSQUEDA. 
  The managerial decision, which is known as "general leave," 
was ordered by the Navy command for the period from 24 December 
to 2 January. Essential Navy services were not discontinued. 
  A government source said that the Navy was facing "serious" 
economic problems, noting that "it has debts" and "had asked the 
government for an advance, which was not granted." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

