<H3> <TI>   Human Rights Leader Criticizes U.S. Embassy `Onslaught' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1201131194 La Paz Radio Fides Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1201131194 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Radio Fides Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Edwin Mallon Avalos, the Radio Fides </F>
correspondent in Cochabamba] 
  [Text] During a news conference, the Permanent Assembly 
for Human Rights [APDH], along with various groups such as 
peasant organizations and the Departmental Workers Federation, 
reported a U.S. Embassy onslaught against those who dare to 
report DEA abuses in our national territory. 
  This remark was made by Dr. Victor Gutierrez, the APDH 
president in Cochabamba. 

