<F P=100> NAFTA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas, Canadian Trade Minister Review NAFTA </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601162594 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari received Roy 
MacLaren, Canadian international trade minister, during his 
visit to Mexico. During a news conference held after the 
meeting, the Canadian minister announced the Mexican, U.S., and 
Canadian trade ministers will meet on 14 January in Mexico City 
to analyze issues such as subsidies and anti-dumping and to 
establish a mechanism, before the end of 1994, so other 
countries may join the North American Free Trade Agreement. He 
said Chile will be the next country to join NAFTA, but he said 
it is open to all the countries in the world that fulfill its 
requirements. 

</TEXT>

