<H3> <TI>   Fuel Shipment Scheduled, Postponed, Rescheduled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1201172094 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1201172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the national level, the news is the announcement 
of the arrival, then the postponement, then the arrival of the 
humanitarian fuel shipment. 
  First, there was the announcement last week by American 
Ambassador Lawrence Pezzullo, special delegate on the Haitian 
crisis of the U.S. secretary of state, of the arrival of the 
humanitarian oil shipment for 12 January. The United States then 
announced at the last minute, on 11 January, the postponement of 
the shipment, with no explanation. 
  This morning, an OAS spokesman made an announcement to the 
contrary. There is therefore confusion on the arrival of the 
shipment. 

</TEXT>

