<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Instructors Reportedly Training Rebels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201152794 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1201152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The Awakening" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Military spokesmen in Managua who asked not to be 
identified said on 11 January that a group of 300 Nicaraguans 
are being trained in Honduran territory by U.S. instructors. 
The soldiers, who demanded that their names not be revealed, 
said the rebels, presumably anti-Sandinists, are being trained 
by two U.S. instructors. According to the sources, the rebels 
receiving military training are based in Yamales, near the 
Nicaraguan-Honduran border. They added that the rebels receive 
supplies every two days in a helicopter identified as an HLH 
[expansion unknown]. 

</TEXT>

