<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Institution of Value-Added Tax </TI></H3>
<H4>   Caracas Mayor: VAT `Unconstitutional' </H4>
<F P=102> PA1301175494 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1301175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Today, Caracas Mayor Aristobulo Isturiz presented a 
request for annulment of the VAT law to the political and 
administrative division of the Supreme Court of Justice because 
he feels it is unconstitutional. He will also present a writ of 
amparo calling for the suspendion of the VAT collection in his 
jurisdiction while the Supreme Court issues a ruling. 
  According to Mayor Isturiz, the law is unconstitutional 
because tax issues are the exclusive responsibility of the 
national Congress and therefore its approval cannot be delegated 
to others. In addition, modifications to the tax system should 
be done in a progressive manner and not the way it has been done. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

