<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reaction to Institution of Value-Added Tax </TI></H3>
<H4>   Congressman Wants Reform </H4>
<F P=102> PA1301175694 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1301175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Congressman Reinaldo Cervini has pointed out that 
the VAT is a regressive and unconstitutional measure that must 
be reformed. 
  [Begin Cervini recording] Measures, such as price controls, 
just seek to please the people for the time being. If there was 
really a serious interest in controlling prices, the correct 
thing to do would have been to regulate bank interests as well 
as the costs of electricity, telephones, and transportation. In 
addition, measures should have been taken to control the prices 
businessmen pay for Central Bank bonds, and this would then lead 
to a just control of prices. 
  What is being done now will bring negative consequences for 
the national producers. The measure is strictly to please the 
people, but it is not being handled properly. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

