<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports From 7-13 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1301174394 </F>
<F P=103> PY1301174394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Brazil monitored between 7 and 
13 January. 
  Fuel prices increased 17 percent as of 0000 on 11 January. 
This is the first increase of the year authorized by the Finance 
Ministry. Now fuel prices will not have any real readjustments, 
but will be readjusted according to the monthly inflation rate. 
National airline tickets were increased 31 percent. (Brasilia 
Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in Portuguese 0900 GMT 11 Jan 
94) 
  The Trade Technical Department reported that Brazilian wood 
exports were $800 million in 1993 compared with $562 million in 
1992. (Sao Paulo GAZETA MERCANTIL in Portuguese 11 Jan 94 p 13) 

