<H3> <TI>   President Swears In New DF Attorney General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1401044294 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0030 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1401044294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vector 21" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Correspondent Elizabeth Diaz Otero reported that 
President Carlos Salinas de Gortari appointed Humberto Benitez 
Trevino as new Attorney General in the Federal District [DF] of 
Mexico and our reporter Jesus Cazasola has been closely 
following the swearing-in. Go ahead Jesus: 
  [Cazasola] Yes, Ana Patricia, good afternoon. Both the 
rulers and the ruled must be subject to the empire of the law. 
No one should act beyond the law because the country's 
conditions so demand. Humberto Benitez Trevino said this after 
being sworn in as new DF attorney general. He said there will 
be no truce for crime and added that no economic or human 
resources will be spared to guarantee the security the people of 
Mexico City demand. He said he will act with energy wherever 
there is impunity. 
  Humberto Benitez Trevino took over from Rene Gonzalez de la 
Vega who in turn was appointed deputy prosecutor for preliminary 
enquiries [sub-procurador de averiguaciones previas] for the 
Attorney General's Office. 
  The new DF attorney general said that the firm hand of the 
law will be wherever impunity is detected. He also called on 
the institution's public servants to act strictly according to 
the Constitution, otherwise the corresponding punishment will be 
applied. 

</TEXT>

