<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Reports `Complete Calm' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1401015694 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0030 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1401015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jesus Cazasola; from the "Vector 21" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The National Defense Secretariat reported that in 
compliance with presidential orders, troops operating in upper 
Chiapas State to counter action by law breakers have 
concentrated in the villages or towns of Rancho Nuevo, San 
Cristobal de las Casas, Ocosingo, Altamirano, near Las 
Margaritas, Comitan, Chanal, San Juan Chamula, and Tuxtla 
Gutierrez, Chiapas State. 
  The military personnel continue to perform social work in 
some of these communities, especially water and food 
distribution chores, as well as the distribution of other 
primary articles. 
  The Mexican Army soldiers continue to patrol the various 
communities to prevent possible attacks on the residents. Up to 
now no armed group has been seen. The National Defense 
Secretariat report concludes by stating that there is complete 
calm. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

