<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Callejas Rejects Suspending General Discua </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1401043194 Tegucigalpa LA TRIBUNA in Spanish 11 Jan 94 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> PA1401043194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tegucigalpa LA TRIBUNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Rafael Leonardo Callejas reiterated 
yesterday, that the legal conditions to suspend Armed Forces 
Commander General Luis Alonso Discua Elvir are nonexistent. 
Thus, he said, the Committee of Relatives of Missing Detainees 
in Honduras's (COFADEH) petition in this respect is inadmissible. 
  "No private organization has the power to order the 
suspension of the Armed Forces commander. This action can only 
be ordered by the corresponding legal authority," he emphasized. 
  Callejas, in his role as general commander of the Salvadoran 
Armed Forces, opened the session of the Armed Forces Senior 
Council this morning. 

</TEXT>

