<H3> <TI>   Government `To Show Solidarity' With CFA States </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1301111594 Paris LE MONDE in French 13 Jan 94 p 14 </F>
<F P=103> BR1301111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE MONDE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique jointly released by the Presidential Office and </F>
the Prime Minister's Office the evening of 11 January on the 
devaluation of the CFA franc] 
  [Text] The heads of state and of government of the African 
countries in the franc zone have decided to modify the parity of 
the CFA franc and the Comoran franc in relation to the French 
franc. France has given its agreement to this decision which 
aims to restore the right conditions for lasting economic growth 
by enabling the resumption of international funding. This 
decision will consolidate the recovery efforts in which many 
countries in the franc zone are already involved. 
  France, which is in the front rank of the international 
financial community, will not fail to show its solidarity with 
its partners. To this end, it will closely follow and 
participate in the implementation of the necessary accompaying 
measures, particularly those intended to support the most 
underprivileged populations. 
  France will step up its effort to promote economic and 
social 
development. New measures to cancel and reduce the debt have 
also been decided in continuation of the action taken in this 
sphere by President Francois Mitterrand. These different 
measures bear witness to France's resolute and tangible support 
for the franc zone and to the preferential ties it maintains 
with its partners." 

</TEXT>

