<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Others Protest School Funding Bill </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mitterrand Criticizes Balladur </H4>
<F P=102> AU1301182994 Paris AFP in English 1244 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1301182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Paris, Jan 13 (AFP) -- President Francois 
Mitterrand waded into France's "war of the schools" on Thursday 
[13 January], attacking conservative Prime Minister Edouard 
Balladur and cheering on the left ahead of a massive 
demonstration planned for Sunday. 
  The socialist president condemned Balladur's "unfortunate 
initiative" in rushing a bill through the senate that granted 
unlimited use of public funds to the country's private, mainly 
Catholic, schools. 
  In an interview with the socialist weekly VENDREDI, 
Mitterrand said the state education system felt unfairly treated 
and that he "understood" the anger of teachers and parents. 
  Teachers unions and parents associations as well as 
left-wing 
organisations are planning a big demonstration against the new 
legislation on Sunday and hope to draw 300,000 people on to the 
Paris boulevards. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

