<H3> <TI>   DEA Members, Foreign Personnel Said Involved in Operation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1601031994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0133 GMT 16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1601031994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Javier Arango in Rio Blanco, Tolima Department; </F>
from the "TV Today" newscast] 
  [Text] An operation was executed this week in Rio Blanco, 
southern Tolima Department, presumably with the participation of 
DEA members. Witnesses say six helicopters landed with troops, 
while two small airplanes overflew the zone. 
  The helicopters landed, one by one, and deposited troops in 
the village. Certain residences were later raided. Aircraft 
also overflew the area, and helicopters landed in Gaitan, a 
poppy and guerrilla forces center located two hours from Rio 
Blanco. 
  [Begin Hernando Cardenas recording] It has been confirmed 
that people's money has been seized. It is known that one 
person's 10 million pesos were taken. [end recording] 
  People living in this zone of Tolima Department say the 
country's authorities are doing the right thing when they 
provide protection, but they wonder: Why was such an impressive 
operation launched? Why did the operation include foreign 
personnel? 
  [Begin recording] [Father Ivan Rodriguez] I saw helicopters 
flying overhead. It is true, there were some foreigners. 
  [Jesus Valbuena] The commanders were people who spoke very 
little, and they were heard speaking some words in English. [end 
recording] 
  The residents of Rio Blanco are used to many difficult 
situations, but they are still perplexed by this operation. 

</TEXT>

