<F P=102>  PA1701180894 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1740 GMT 17 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1701180894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Santa Fe de Bogota, 17 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- Police 
reported today that the Colombian guerrillas kidnapped two U.S. 
citizens who were involved in missionary activities in southern 
Colombia. The missionaries were kidnapped in reprisal for the 
arrival of U.S. soldiers in Colombia. 
  Official sources consulted by NOTIMEX indicated that a group 
of 20 rebels of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia 
(FARC) intercepted the vehicle in which missionaries Steven 
Welch, 41, and Timothy Vandyke, 40, were traveling in southern 
Meta Department. 
  According to the report, the two were kidnapped over the 
weekend on the road from Villavicencio to Restrepo, 200 km from 
this capital. 
  Although the police did not indicate the reason for the 
kidnapping, local unofficial sources said the rebels said it was 
in reprisal for the presence of a U.S. military contingent in 
the Puerto Lopez area, near the site of the kidnapping. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

