<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Politician Critical After Attack by `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1401160094 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1950 GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1401160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cartagena de Indias (Colombia), 13 Jan (EFE) -- 
Police report that some unidentified gunmen shot Colombian 
Liberal politician Jorge Luis Horta, who is running for the 
Senate, in Cartagena de Indias on 13 January. 
  Colonel Hector Mario Castro, police commander in Bolivar 
Department, whose capital is Cartagena, said that the attack 
took place some time after 1200 in the neighborhood of San 
Felipe Castle on Pedro de Heredia Avenue. 
  According to Col. Castro, the attackers, who were on a 
motorcycle, intercepted Horta's vehicle and shot him. However, 
at that moment, a police patrol came along and prevented the 
terrorists from accomplishing their objective, which was 
seemingly to assassinate him. 
  Following a confrontation between the criminals and 
policemen, the criminals fled while the patrol took Horta to the 
Cartagena de Indias University Hospital. Horta was shot in the 
chin, neck, and a hand. 
  Col. Castro stated that the reasons for the attack are 
unknown, and that although Horta remained conscious while he was 
being taken to the hospital, his health condition is critical. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

