<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Hommes Uninjured in Assassination Attempt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1701144894 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1409 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1701144894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finance Minister Rudolf Hommes was uninjured in a 
bomb attack staged by individuals in an attempt to assassinate 
him. By chance, General Octavio Vargas Silva's car was passing 
by and his driver immediately went to the aid of the finance 
minister and drove him away. The minister has not yet spoken to 
reporters, but we are told that he has just telephoned President 
Cesar Gaviria to inform him of the incidents that occurred this 
morning at 0800. 
  [Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network at 1419 GMT on 
17 January adds that the finance minister was traveling 
eastbound in a gray BMW with license plate AH-4772. A bomb 
exploded as the vehicle was about to cross the bridge on 5th 
Avenue. The left part of the car was severely damaged. 
According to reports received by Caracol, the explosive device 
that was planted beside a utility pole contained between five 
and six kg of dynamite. The Santa Fe de Bogota Metropolitan 
Police and Administrative Department of Security experts are 
currently evaluating the situation and are trying to determine 
what type of bomb it was.] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

