<H3> <TI>   Report Details Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1701195094 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1701195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Rudolf Hommes, finance and credit minister, escaped 
an attempt on his life unhurt, but one of his bodyguards was 
injured. "National" newscast was the first to arrive at the 
scene. Here is a report by J.J. Pinilla. 
  [Pinilla] The attack took place at 0805 [1305 GMT], when 
Minister Rudolf Hommes was on his usual trip from his home to 
his office in midtown Santa Fe de Bogota. One policeman was 
wounded. The charge, consisting of over 10 kg of ammonal, was 
placed at the base of a lamppost on 26th Street and 5th Avenue 
and detonated by remote control. Following the explosion, the 
minister's driver continued on for another block despite the 
fact that one of the car's tires was flat. They stopped at the 
Santa Monica Hotel, where Hommes Rodriguez left the vehicle and 
was taken to his office in another vehicle. 
  [Begin recording] [Police Colonel Miguel Angel Meza] He was 
taken directly to his office. 
  [Reporter] What happened to the policeman. [Meza not heard 
to 
answer] 
  [Reporter] What route were they taking? Where was the 
minister going? 
  [Meza] He was going to his office. [end recording] 
  [Pinilla] A police bodyguard identified as Libardo Arias was 
injured. A mass transit bus and a private vehicle that were 
passing by were damaged. 
  [Begin recording] [Bus driver Enrique Molano] [Words 
indistinct] just leave me alone. 
  [Reporter] How did you react when the bomb exploded? 
  [Molano] I put on the brakes because the lamppost fell on 
top 
of the bus. That is all I saw. Smoke filled the bus. [end 
recording] 
  [Pinilla] The severity of the attack was lessened thanks to 
the skill of the minister's driver, who never stopped the 
vehicle despite the explosion. 

</TEXT>

