<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Appoints New Economic Development Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1701225294 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 2058 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1701225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 17 Jan (DPA) -- Colombian 
President Cesar Gaviria appointed today young politician 
Mauricio Cardenas as the new economic development minister, 
Narino Government Palace sources have told DPA. 
  The new minister is the son of Jorge Cardenas, Colombian 
coffee czar, and he currently holds the post of manager of the 
Colombian State Energy Enterprise. 
  This will be his second experience in the public sector, 
because previously he had dedicated himself exclusively to 
managing private sector companies. 
  Cardenas must carry out an industrial reconversion process 
initiated by his predecessor. The process is aimed at boosting 
industry in the face of the economic opening implemented by 
Gaviria's government. 
  The incumbent minister resigned to join the political 
campaign of Conservative candidate Andres Pastrana, who in early 
February will launch officially his presidential campaign. 

</TEXT>

